    "A is a V-BAO iff each ■ i operatoris completely multiplicative, i.e., for every i ∈ I and X ⊆ A, if x∈X x exists in ⟨A, ≤⟩, then x∈X ■ i x exists in ⟨A, ≤⟩ and x∈X■ i x = ■ i x∈X x;4.",
    "A is a T -BAO iff each ■ i operator admits a left adjoint, i.e., there is a functionf i: A → A such that for all x, y ∈ A, x ≤ ■ i y iff f i (x) ≤ y.",
    "◁Since A is a BAO, parts 3-4 could be equivalently stated in terms of and ♦ i instead of and ■ i.",
    "For part 3, the equivalent condition is that each ♦ i is completely additive:if x∈X x exists in ⟨A, ≤⟩, then x∈X ♦ i x exists in ⟨A, ≤⟩ and x∈X ♦ i x = ♦ i x∈Xx.",
    "For part 4, the equivalent condition is that there is a function g i: A → A such that for all x, y ∈ A, ♦ i x ≤ y iff x ≤ g i (y)."
